# Paywalled Blog Demo -- Implementation Plan

## 1. Project Overview and Architecture

The project is a Next.js App Router application with TypeScript and Tailwind CSS. It integrates three external services -- Sanity CMS (content), Stripe (payments), and ThirdWeb (wallet-based auth) -- and provides a fully functional visual demo at `/demo` that works even when environment variables are absent.

**Root directory:** `/Users/josephgenest/Desktop/MercorSprint31926/model_b`

---

## 2. Complete File Tree

```
/
├── .env.local.example              # Template for all env vars
├── .gitignore
├── next.config.ts
├── package.json
├── postcss.config.mjs
├── tailwind.config.ts
├── tsconfig.json
│
├── public/
│   └── fonts/
│       ├── futura-medium.woff2     # Futura for titles (self-hosted or fallback)
│       └── futura-bold.woff2
│
├── sanity/
│   ├── env.ts                      # Sanity env var reader with fallbacks
│   ├── lib/
│   │   ├── client.ts               # createClient from next-sanity
│   │   ├── queries.ts              # GROQ queries (posts, authors)
│   │   └── image.ts                # @sanity/image-url helper
│   └── schemas/
│       ├── index.ts                # Schema registry (exports schemaTypes array)
│       ├── post.ts                 # Post document type
│       └── author.ts               # Author document type
│
├── sanity.config.ts                # Sanity Studio configuration (defineConfig)
│
